            <h2 class="text-white"> What is Dolby Atmos </h2>

            <p class="text-white">
                <img src="https://i.imgur.com/yvLA65X.jpg" alt="Screen" style="width:60%;height:60%;margin-left:15px;">
                Dolby Atmos is a new sound technology developed in 2012 by Dolby, the new technology
                expands the 5.1 and 7.1 previous setups into more speakers placed all around the room
                to create an all-surrounding 3D-sound experience. Basically, Atmos is the latest way
                to get surrounded by sound, one of the main benefits of this new technology is that
                it can work with as many or as few speakers as you have.
                With Dolby Atmos, and surrounding sound systems, filmmakers don’t deal with channels anymore, 
                instead, they treat the sound as an object, for example in the picture below, when 
                the characters look to the left corner of the room, which is the source of the sound, 
                the audience will hear the sound from this left corner
            </p>

